WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.433
See how you can use Knox Manage dynamic group syntax

2
00:00:03.433 --> 00:00:09.533
which allows you to define complex conditions for automatic membership for your groups!

3
00:00:09.533 --> 00:00:13.133
Go to 'Knox Manage' from the left navigation pane.

4
00:00:13.133 --> 00:00:15.133


5
00:00:15.133 --> 00:00:19.533
Go to 'Groups' where you manage device and user collections.

6
00:00:19.533 --> 00:00:21.533


7
00:00:21.533 --> 00:00:23.299
Click 'Create Group'.

8
00:00:23.300 --> 00:00:24.766


9
00:00:24.766 --> 00:00:26.566
Enter a name for your group.

10
00:00:26.566 --> 00:00:26.866


11
00:00:26.866 --> 00:00:29.666
Select if your group is a User or Device group.

12
00:00:29.666 --> 00:00:30.099


13
00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:36.233
Select 'Dynamic' membership so the group is automatically populated based on rules.

14
00:00:36.233 --> 00:00:36.666


15
00:00:36.666 --> 00:00:39.366
Click 'Next' to move to rule definitions.

16
00:00:39.366 --> 00:00:41.132


17
00:00:41.133 --> 00:00:49.466
Switch to syntax mode by clicking 'Change to syntax mode'. Simple mode limits you to 5 conditions, while Syntax mode lets you write

18
00:00:49.466 --> 00:00:56.132
MVEL-based expressions and use advanced properties that are not available on simple mode. Note that Knox Manage Expression

19
00:00:56.133 --> 00:01:00.199
Language doesn't support all functionalities offered by MVEL.

20
00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:00.233


21
00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:04.666
Click 'CHANGE' to confirm the switch.

22
00:01:04.666 --> 00:01:07.232


23
00:01:07.233 --> 00:01:14.966
In the expression editor, enter your rule conditions. For example, combine device status, enrollment type, platform, and a security

24
00:01:14.966 --> 00:01:22.966
property to check whether the device is password compliant, all in a single expression. The editor supports multiline expressions up to

25
00:01:22.966 --> 00:01:28.332
1,000 characters, allowing you to define complex rules for controlled device targeting.

26
00:01:28.333 --> 00:01:29.133


27
00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:36.433
Then, you can click "Preview devices" to see which devices will be added to your group based on your conditions.

28
00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:40.300


29
00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:47.033
Enable the option to automatically push assigned resources to devices that are added to the group.

30
00:01:47.033 --> 00:01:47.566


31
00:01:47.566 --> 00:01:50.232
Click 'Create' to create your new dynamic group.

32
00:01:50.233 --> 00:01:51.633


33
00:01:51.633 --> 00:01:59.666
Your dynamic group is ready, automatically adding matching devices and pushing assigned profiles and apps instantly. To learn more about

34
00:01:59.666 --> 00:02:07.166
Knox Manage dynamic groups, see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. Thanks for watching!
